---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — Echo 7"
  description="Echo 7 privacy policy. Solvida Ltd trading as Echo 7, registered in England and Wales."
  canonicalPath="/privacy/"
>
  <Nav />
  <main>
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container text-column legal">
        <p class="legal__draft-notice">
          Draft — registered office address pending confirmation from Companies House.
        </p>
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="legal__updated">Last updated: 25 June 2026</p>

        <p>
          Echo 7 is a trading name of Solvida Ltd, a company registered in England and Wales
          (company number 7232433), with its registered office at
          <span class="legal__placeholder">&lt;registered address&gt;</span>. Solvida Ltd is
          the data controller responsible for your personal data.
        </p>

        <p>
          This policy explains what information we collect when you use this website or get
          in touch with us, the lawful basis on which we process it, how long we keep it, and
          the rights you have under UK data protection law.
        </p>

        <h2>Who we are and how to contact us</h2>
        <p>
          If you have any questions about this policy or about how we handle your personal
          data, you can contact us at <a href="mailto:hello@echo7.io">hello@echo7.io</a> or by
          writing to us at the registered address above.
        </p>

        <h2>What we collect</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>Information you give us.</strong> When you submit the contact form on this
          site, we collect the information you provide directly: your name, business email
          address, phone number (if given), company name, job title (if given), and the
          message you write to us.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Information collected automatically.</strong> We collect standard analytics
          data about how visitors use this site, such as pages viewed, approximate location,
          device and browser type, and how you arrived at the site. This is collected via
          Google Analytics and through cookies (see <em>Cookies</em> below).
        </p>

        <h2>How we use your information and our lawful basis</h2>
        <table class="legal__table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Activity</th>
              <th>Purpose</th>
              <th>Lawful basis (UK GDPR)</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td>Responding to contact form enquiries</td>
              <td>To answer your enquiry and correspond with you</td>
              <td>Legitimate interests (Article 6(1)(f)) — responding to a request you have made</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Managing an ongoing client relationship</td>
              <td>To deliver services, manage the engagement, and administer payments</td>
              <td>Performance of a contract (Article 6(1)(b))</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Keeping financial and accounting records</td>
              <td>To meet our legal obligations to HMRC and Companies House</td>
              <td>Legal obligation (Article 6(1)(c))</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Website analytics</td>
              <td>To understand how the site is used and to improve it</td>
              <td>Consent (Article 6(1)(a)), obtained via our cookie banner</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        <p>
          We do not sell, rent, or share your information with third parties for marketing
          purposes.
        </p>

        <h2>Cookies</h2>
        <p>
          This website uses cookies. Strictly necessary cookies are required for the site to
          function. Analytics cookies (set by Google Analytics) are only placed with your
          consent, which you give through the cookie banner when you first visit the site.
          You can withdraw or change your consent at any time via
          <span class="legal__placeholder">&lt;cookie settings link / mechanism&gt;</span>.
          For more detail, see our <span class="legal__placeholder">&lt;Cookie Policy&gt;</span>.
        </p>

        <h2>Data Security</h2>
        <p>
          We have put in place appropriate security measures to prevent your personal data
          from being accidentally lost, used, accessed in an unauthorised way, altered, or
          disclosed. Access to your data is limited to those employees, agents, and
          contractors who have a business need to know.
        </p>

        <h2>How long we keep your information</h2>
        <p>We do not keep personal data for longer than necessary. Our retention periods are:</p>
        <ul class="legal__list">
          <li><strong>Enquiries that do not become client relationships:</strong> 12 months from the date of last contact, after which they are deleted.</li>
          <li><strong>Client relationship records:</strong> for the duration of the engagement and for 6 years after it ends.</li>
          <li><strong>Financial and accounting records:</strong> 6 years from the end of the financial year to which they relate, in line with HMRC requirements.</li>
          <li><strong>Analytics data:</strong> retained by Google Analytics for 14 months, in line with our configured retention setting.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Where it is stored and who processes it</h2>
        <p>
          Contact form submissions and client records are stored securely in our customer
          relationship management (CRM) system and email servers. Analytics data is processed
          by Google Analytics. We also use third-party service providers to host our website
          and IT infrastructure. These providers act as our processors and process your data
          only on our documented instructions.
        </p>

        <h2>International transfers</h2>
        <p>
          Some of our processors, including Google Analytics, may transfer and store data
          outside the UK, including in the United States. Where this happens, we ensure an
          appropriate safeguard is in place — such as a UK adequacy regulation, the UK
          extension to the EU–US Data Privacy Framework, or the International Data Transfer
          Agreement (IDTA) / Standard Contractual Clauses — so that your data receives an
          equivalent level of protection.
        </p>

        <h2>Automated decision-making</h2>
        <p>
          We do not carry out automated decision-making or profiling that produces legal
          effects concerning you or that similarly significantly affects you. All decisions
          about your enquiry or engagement are made by a person.
        </p>

        <h2>Your rights</h2>
        <p>Under UK GDPR, you have the right to:</p>
        <ul class="legal__list">
          <li>ask what personal data we hold about you (access);</li>
          <li>request the correction of inaccurate data (rectification);</li>
          <li>request the deletion of your data (erasure);</li>
          <li>object to or restrict how we process your data;</li>
          <li>request the transfer of your data to you or another provider (portability);</li>
          <li>withdraw your consent at any time, where we rely on consent (this does not affect processing carried out before withdrawal).</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          To exercise any of these rights, contact us at
          <a href="mailto:hello@echo7.io">hello@echo7.io</a>. We will respond within one month.
        </p>

        <h2>Complaints</h2>
        <p>
          If you are unhappy with how we have handled your personal data, you have the right
          to complain to the Information Commissioner's Office (ICO):
        </p>
        <ul class="legal__list">
          <li>Website: <a href="https://ico.org.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">ico.org.uk</a></li>
          <li>Helpline: 0303 123 1113</li>
        </ul>
        <p>We would ask that you contact us first so we have the opportunity to put things right.</p>

        <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this policy from time to time. The date at the top shows when it was
          last revised.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal {
    padding-block: var(--space-md);
  }

  .legal__draft-notice {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
    padding: 0.4rem 0.8rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--colour-accent);
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    color: var(--colour-accent);
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.03em;
  }

  .legal h1 {
    font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 4vw, 2.6rem);
  }

  .legal__updated {
    margin-top: var(--space-sm);
    color: var(--colour-text-muted);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
  }

  .legal h2 {
    margin-top: var(--space-lg);
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    color: var(--colour-accent);
  }

  .legal p {
    margin-top: var(--space-sm);
    color: var(--colour-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .legal a {
    color: var(--colour-accent);
  }

  .legal strong {
    color: var(--colour-text);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .legal__placeholder {
    color: #ff9d6b;
    background: rgba(255, 157, 107, 0.1);
    padding: 0.1rem 0.4rem;
    border-radius: 3px;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .legal__list {
    margin-top: var(--space-sm);
    padding-left: 1.2rem;
    color: var(--colour-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .legal__list li {
    margin-top: 0.4rem;
  }

  .legal__table {
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    font-size: 0.92rem;
  }

  .legal__table th,
  .legal__table td {
    text-align: left;
    padding: 0.7rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--colour-hairline);
    vertical-align: top;
  }

  .legal__table th {
    color: var(--colour-accent);
    font-weight: 600;
    background: rgba(232, 230, 240, 0.03);
  }

  .legal__table td {
    color: var(--colour-text-muted);
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .legal__table {
      font-size: 0.85rem;
    }
  }
</style>
